      <scopecontent id="aspace_f16f8cb3b3893314aaedb1e6fb47e4c6">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>One digital copy of an audiorecording, with transcript, of an interview with Thomas Wilfred conducted on 1968 July 18 at New York Public Radio (WNYC) by Patricia Marx.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_bddf314cade68cceb2c019a22ccf99af">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>New York Public Radio is a non-profit corporation, incorporated in 1979. New York Public Radio is the owner of WNYC and other New York-area radio stations.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <bioghist id="aspace_0090561bcc7182a2cb9ed5f25364d1e7">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Thomas Wilfred (1889-1968), kinetic light artist whose body of work consists of compositions that he called "Lumia."</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <bioghist id="aspace_1aac408f4deaa9a235bd28e1171f5f27">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Patricia Marx, interviewer at WNYC.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <arrangement id="aspace_dbcbf895c093542f33fcb94fecd4e7aa">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The material is arranged as received from the donor.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_47e3c6bc5352e4b37bb1a7eafa060d1d"
                      localtype="RestrictedSpecColl">
